The paper deals with the algorithmic problem of testing digital convexity, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of running time, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation). The paper also discusses the convex hull computation, which is a well-known problem in discrete mathematics, indicating that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper presents a polynomial algorithm, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
